    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects use of a single ASTM F1717 offset distance; this is accepted because the 40 mm offset is the regulatory standard worst-case condition and the shortfall does not materially undermine confidence in the FEA predictions for the declared COU. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; relative difference <10%). Package is submitted under ProfileMinimal with hash integrity assurance; signature workflow is pending completion of the institutional digital-signing process.",
